\par Gain Psionic Focus: }{Merely holding a reservoir of psionic power points in mind gives psionic characters a special energy. Psionic characters can put that energy to work without actually paying a power point cost\emdash 
they can become psionically focused as a special use of the Concentration skill.
\par If you have 1 or more power points available, you can meditate to attempt to become psionically f
ocused. The DC to become psionically focused is 20. Meditating is a full-round action that provokes attacks of opportunity. When you are psionically focused, you can expend your focus on any single Concentration check you make thereafter. When you expend 
your focus in this manner, your Concentration check is treated as if you rolled a 15. It\rquote s like taking 10, except that the number you add to your Concentration modifier is 15. You can also expend your focus to gain the benefit of a psionic feat
\emdash many psionic feats are activated in this way.
\par Once you are psionically focused, you remain focused until you expend your focus, become unconscious, or go to sleep (or enter a meditative trance, in the case of elans), or until your power point reserve drops to 0.
\par }{\b Action:}{ Usually none. In most cases, making a Concentration check doesn\rquote 
t require an action; it is either a free action (when attempted reactively) or part of another action (when attempted actively). Meditating to gain psionic focus is a full-round action.
\par }{\b Try Again:}{ Yes, though a success doesn\rquote t cancel the effects of a previous failure, such as the loss of the power points for a power being manifested or the disruption of a power being concentrated on.
\par }{\b Special:}{ You can use Concentration to manifest a power or use a psi-like ability defensively, so as to avoid attacks of opportunity altogether. The DC of the check is 15 + the power\rquote 
s level. If the Concentration check succeeds, you can manifest normally without provoking any attacks of opportunity. If the Concent
ration check fails, the power also automatically fails and the power points are wasted, just as if your concentration had been disrupted by a distraction.
\par A character with the Combat Manifestation feat gets a +4 bonus on Concentration checks made to manifest a power or use a psi-like ability while on the defensive or while grappling or pinned.
\par }{\b Synergy:}{ If you have 5 or more ranks in Concentration, you get a +2 bonus on Autohypnosis checks.
